<subSubSection id="CCFD0CC3FFF7014B63A5F70897438AB7" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="84585F48FFF7014B63A5F70897438AB7" blockId="21.[151,760,1800,2047]" lastBlockId="21.[828,1437,190,405]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B63A5F70892688C3D" bold="true" box="[151,281,1800,1823]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Comments.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6213F70892B88C3D" author="JACOBY M." box="[289,457,1800,1823]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="377 - 501" part="36" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." title="Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
described this species from two specimens and classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B613BF72891FB8C1D" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1864" box="[521,650,1832,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B613BF72891FB8C1D" box="[521,650,1832,1855]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Platyxantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This was followed by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6225F74892D58C7D" author="WEISE J." box="[279,420,1864,1887]" editor="SCHENKLING S." firstAuthor="WEISE" journalOrPublisher="Berlin" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref33576" refString="WEISE J. 1924: Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. W. Junk, Berlin, pp. 1 - 225." title="Pars 78: Chrysomelidae: 13. Galerucinae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus" year="1924">WEISE (1924)</bibRefCitation>
. For an unknown reason, 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6195F74893AF8C5D" author="WILCOX J. A." editor="WILCOX J. A." firstAuthor="WILCOX" journalOrPublisher="Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="433 - 664" refId="ref33616" refString="WILCOX J. A. 1973: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina. In: WILCOX J. A. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3). Editio seconda. W. Junk, ' s-Gravenhage, pp. 433 - 664." title="Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae: Luperini: Luperina" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Coleopterorum Catalogus Supplementa. Pars 78 (3)." year="1973">WILCOX (1973)</bibRefCitation>
classified it in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B62B2F76892948C5D" authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" box="[384,485,1896,1919]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B62B2F76892948C5D" box="[384,485,1896,1919]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which probably caused it to be omitted by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6260F78892A78CBD" author="REID C. A. M." box="[338,470,1928,1951]" firstAuthor="REID" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Entomology" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 9" part="38" refId="ref33192" refString="REID C. A. M. 1999: Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae). Australian Journal of Entomology 38: 1 - 9." title="Reappraisal of the genus Taumacera Thunberg with descriptions of two new species from South-East Asia (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Galerucinae)" type="journal article" year="1999">REID (1999)</bibRefCitation>
. I examined both 
<typeStatus id="5B5CE1EAFFF7014B61A8F78891868CBD" box="[666,759,1928,1951]" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">syntypes</typeStatus>
(females) deposited in the BMNH and MSNG. Because the assignment in 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B626BF7C892CF8CFD" authorityName=", MOHAMEDSAID" authorityYear="1998" box="[345,446,1992,2015]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Polexima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B626BF7C892CF8CFD" box="[345,446,1992,2015]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Polexima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is evidently wrong as it is an African genus, I tentatively transfer 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6102F7E891A98CDD" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[560,728,2024,2047]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6102F7E891A98CDD" box="[560,728,2024,2047]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B600EF0BE90C28BF7" authorityName="Thunberg" authorityYear="1814" box="[828,947,190,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taumacera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B600EF0BE90C28BF7" box="[828,947,190,213]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Taumacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the correct generic placement can only be resolved when a male is discovered.As mentioned already by 
<bibRefCitation id="E07622B9FFF7014B6086F0FE972A8A37" author="JACOBY M." box="[948,1115,254,277]" firstAuthor="JACOBY" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" pagination="377 - 501" part="36" refId="ref31521" refString="JACOBY M. 1896 a: Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 36: 377 - 501." title="Descriptions of the new genera and species of phytophagous Coleoptera obtained by Dr. Modigliani in Sumatra" type="journal article" year="1896" yearSuffix="a">JACOBY (1896a)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B6750F0FE961F8A37" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1122,1390,254,277]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multicostata">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B6750F0FE961F8A37" box="[1122,1390,254,277]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">Platyxantha multicostata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="43E724CBFFF7014B600EF11E90918A17" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1896" box="[828,992,286,309]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Platyxantha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="submetallica">
<emphasis id="B693835AFFF7014B600EF11E90918A17" box="[828,992,286,309]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="44">P. submetallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could belong to a single species as they were collected at the same locality (Si-Rambé) and differ only in the body length and paler colouration of the elytral disc in 
